**1 Solution** - using sorting and no additional space
*Time - O(n•logn)*
*Spase - O(1)*
```
class Solution {
    public int removeCoveredIntervals(int[][] intervals) {
        int size = intervals.length;
        if (size <= 1) return size;
		// sort in ASC order by start of interval. and in DESC by end of interval
		// in this case biggest interval will be in the beginning
        Arrays.sort(intervals, (a, b) -> a[0] == b[0] ? b[1] - a[1] : a[0] - b[0]);
		// at least one intervall will be
        int counter = 1;
        int[] prev = intervals[0];

        for (int r = 1; r < size; r++) {
            int[] next = intervals[r];
			// if prev coverst next - just continue
            if (prev[0] <= next[0] && prev[1] >= next[1]) {
                continue;
            }
            // in other case shift reference and inc counter
            prev = next;
            counter++;
        }
        return counter;
    }
}
```

**2 Solution** - using Priority queue.
*Time - O(n•logn)*
Queue Create - about O(n) time
Queue poll 1 item - will be logn. So in sum - O(n•logn) - correct me if I am wrong
*Spase - O(n)* - however it is just a reference to a Queue. which works with references. So we could assume it O(1)
```
class Solution {
    public int removeCoveredIntervals(int[][] intervals) {
        int size = intervals.length;
        if (size <= 1) return size;
		// sort in ASC order by start of interval. and in DESC by end of interval
		// in this case biggest interval will be in the beginning
        PriorityQueue<int[]> queue = new PriorityQueue<>((a, b) -> a[0] == b[0] ? b[1] - a[1] : a[0] - b[0]);
        for (int r = 0; r < size; r++) {
            queue.add(intervals[r]);
        }

		// at least one intervall will be
        int counter = 1;
        int[] prev = queue.poll();
        while(!queue.isEmpty()) {
            int[] next = queue.poll();
			// if prev coverst next - just continue
            if (prev[0] <= next[0] && prev[1] >= next[1]) {
                continue;
            }
            // in other case shift reference and inc counter
            prev = next;
            counter++;
        }
        return counter;
    }
}
```

