# 1. Simple JAVA Solution
- In this solution, We start from second last row and update each element in the current row of the grid by adding the smallest element in the next row and by not considering the element adjacent to the current element(the element which is right below the current element).
- When all the rows will be traversed, we'll have the minimum path sum for each element in the first row of the grid.
- Using this we'll find the smallest element in the first row which will be our result.

        class Solution {
            public int minFallingPathSum(int[][] grid) {
                int minSum = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
                int n = grid.length;
                if(n==1)return grid[0][0];

                for(int i=n-2;i>=0;i--){

                    for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                        int min = minNum(grid, j, i+1, n);
                        grid[i][j] +=min;
                    }
                }
                for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                    minSum =Math.min(minSum, grid[0][i]);
                }

                return minSum;

            }

            // finding the smallest element in (i+1)th row 
            public int minNum(int[][] grid, int index, int row, int n){
                int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
                for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                    if(i!=index){
                        min = Math.min(min,grid[row][i]);
                    }
                }
                return min;
            }
        }


# 2. Recursion and DP:


        class Solution {
            public int minFallingPathSum(int[][] grid) {
                int n = grid.length;
                int dp[][]= new int[n][n]; // fill this matrix withb zeroes
                for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                    for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                        dp[i][j]=-1;
                    }
                }

                // function which will return the minimum sum 
                int minSum = helper(0, -1, n, grid, dp);
                return minSum;
            }

            //method to caculate the minimum sum at each row
            public int helper(int currRow, int prevCol, int n, int[][] grid, int dp[][]){
                if(currRow==n) return 0; // when we've reached the end of the matrix// when the previous element is already filled then return the value of that element
                if(prevCol!=-1 && dp[currRow][prevCol]!=-1) return dp[currRow][prevCol]; 

                int ans = Integer.MAX_VALUE; // store the answer which is minimum of all the sums
                for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                    if(i==prevCol) continue; // when the current column is adjancent to previous column then move to other column

                    // currMin will be the sum of element at current index 
                    // plus minimum sum in next row
                    int currMin = grid[currRow][i] + helper(currRow+1, i , n, grid, dp);

                    ans = Math.min(ans,currMin);
                }
                if(prevCol != -1) dp[currRow][prevCol]= ans;

                return ans;
            }
        }

