# Space Optimization 
- We only need two vectors rather than whole dp array.  
- Prev to store the previously calculated values. 
- Curr to store the minimum path based on previous path sum. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n*m) Traverse the given grid.
- Space complexity: O(N) Just 2 vectors. 

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:

    int minFallingPathSum(vector<vector<int>>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size() ;
        vector<int> prev(n,0), curr(n,0) ;

        // Initialze the first row 
        for( int j=0 ; j<n ; j++ ) prev[j] = arr[0][j]; 

        for(int i = 1; i < arr.size(); ++i){
            for(int j = 0; j < arr[0].size(); ++j){

                curr[j] = INT_MAX;

                for(int k = 0; k < arr[0].size(); ++k){
                    if(j == k)
                        continue;
                    curr[j] = min(prev[k] + arr[i][j],curr[j]);
                }
            }
            prev = curr ;
        }

        int ans = INT_MAX;

