Idea :
- Consider the path as selecting one element from each row satisfying the conditions
- Assume the optimal path contains an arbitrary arr[i][j] . Then the optimal path would choose the lowest optimal path so far from the previous row (excepting column j).
- The final row will contain the smallest paths for all j if element j of the final row was a part of the optimal path.
- Minimum of these will be the answer.

