solutions.content:
I am presenting naive dynamic programming approch which I came up with in , first few minutes.
what dp[i][j] denotes ?
dp[i][j] = minimum falling path if we select grid[i][j].
it means for **botom row** dp[i][j]=grid[i][j] as there is no row below it .
for every other row 
```
dp[i][j]=grid[i][j] + min{ dp[i+1][k] for all k = 0 to n-1 // n is the no. of columns.
```
why this algo ? as for dp[i][j] denotes minimum falling path starting from grid[i][j].
which will be equal to its own value ( grid[i][j] ) + minimum falling path we can get from next row .
**BUT THERE IS MORE TO THIS QUESTION .**
1. to find dp[i][j] we can not use value dp[i+1][j] . Ok we will make slight change .
2. what exactly we get after all this ? Ans dp matrix .
	dp matrix contains values of minimum falling paths . so if we start from i,j then dp[i][j] is the ans.
where to start ? Ans - from first row .
final solution - as we will be starting from first row , now we need to find minimum path 
```so our ans is min. of dp[0][k] // for all k where k= 0 to n-1 where n is no. of columns.```
after doing all this 
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minFallingPathSum(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        int m=grid.size();
        int n=grid[0].size();
        vector<vector<int>> dp(m,vector<int>(n));
        for(int i=m-1;i>=0;i--){
            for(int j=n-1;j>=0;j--){
                if(i==m-1){
                    dp[i][j]=grid[i][j]; // last row 
                }
                else{int temp=0;
                    if(j!=n-1)
                     temp=dp[i+1][j+1]; // initialising temp as needed to find min. you can also set it to some very large value .
                    else{
                        temp=dp[i+1][j-1]; // initialising temp as needed to find min. you can also set it to some very large value .
                    }
                    for(int k=0;k!=n;k++)
                    {   if(k!=j)
                        temp=min(dp[i+1][k],temp);
                    }
                    dp[i][j]=temp+grid[i][j];
                        }
            }
        }
        int temp=dp[0][0];
        for(int i=0;i!=n;i++){
            temp=min(temp,dp[0][i]); // finding minimum from first row .
        }
        return temp;
    }
};
```
