First thought the general approach of traversing the list and counting the elements and then calculating the value bu for efficient code thought of reversing the list and then doing the same
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
Made a function to reverse the list the used the left shift operator to find the power of 2 for tha particular position. 1<<x = 2^x
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: **$$O(N log N)$$** or **$$O(N)$$** depending upon tthe compexity of power of 2
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

