solutions.content:
We can generate all the numbers from 2 digits to 3 digits to 4 digits ...
- `t` means the number of times we are going to loop this layer (i.e. 12, 23, .., 89 -> `t = 8`, 123, 234, ..., 789 -> `t = 7`). Decrement `t` by 1 each loop.
- `inc` is the distance between 2 valid numbers and is always 11 or 111 or 1111 depending on num of digits. Set `inc` to `10 * inc + 1` each loop.
- `start` marks the starting point of each digit: 1, 12, 123, e.g. 1 + 11(inc) = 12, 12 + 111(inc) = 123. Set `start` to `10 * start + 10 - t` each loop.
- `cur` is our current number.
```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> sequentialDigits(int low, int high) {
        int start = 1, cur = 1, inc = 11, t = 8;
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        while(cur <= high){
            for (int i = 0; i < t; i++){
                cur += inc;
                if (cur >= low && cur <= high) ans.add(cur);
            }
            inc = 10 * inc + 1;
            start = 10 * start + 10 - t;
            cur = start;
            t--;
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
```

