solutions.content:
**My approach :**

1. Initially we **generate all the sequences** using the custom `generate()` function
2. Then we **push all the numbers** into `ans` vector which **lies in between `low` and `high` values**

**Explanation :**
		The sequence for 2 digit numbers is --> 12 , 23 , 34, 45 , 56, 67, 78, 89

		which can be seen as  12 + 11 = 23
							  23 + 11 = 34
							  34 + 11 = 45
							  .....
		similarly for 3 digit numbers, base value = 123 and increment = 111
				  for 4 digit numbers, base value = 1234 and increment = 1111
		and so on..

**Condition to stop :**
The last number in any digit sequence will contain the last digit as 9
e.g : 89, 789, 6789.... 123456789

so on adding 1 with 9 will give us 0. This will be our termination condition for our loop
i.e., we loop it  till **`number%10 != 0`**

**C++ solution :**
```
class Solution {
public:
	// generating the sequence
    void generate(int start, int inc,vector<int>& sequence){
        while(start%10!=0){
            sequence.push_back(start);
            start += inc;
        }
    }
    vector<int> sequentialDigits(int low, int high) {
		// starts indicates the initial values of the digits
		// increments indicates the corresponding increment values for the start values of respective digits
        vector<int> starts = {12,123,1234,12345,123456,1234567,12345678};
        vector<int> increments = {11,111,1111,11111,111111,1111111,11111111};

		// we will store the sequence in the sequence vector
        vector<int> sequence;

        for(int i = 0; i < increments.size(); i++){
            generate(starts[i],increments[i],sequence);
        }

        vector<int> ans;
        for(int i = 0; i < sequence.size(); i++){
            if(sequence[i]>= low and sequence[i]<=high)
                ans.push_back(sequence[i]);
        }

		// The  start vector contains upto 8 digits only
		// so we are checking for the 9 digit also and only 123456789 satisfies the sequence
        if(123456789<=high and 123456789>=low)
            ans.push_back(123456789);

        return ans;
    }
};
```

