The idea is to generate all numbers with sequential digits and check if they are in the given range. So start with '1,2,3...9' as most singificant digit and try to generate all possible number by appending a digit one more than previous digit. An example will help in understanding:
```
	let's say: low = 100, high = 300
	start = 1
		num = start
		previousDgit = start
		check if num=1 is in range of (low,high). No, so don't add to answer set.
		try : num*10 + (previousDgit + 1) = 1*10 + (1+1) = 12
			  check if num=12 is in range of (low,high). No, so don't add to answer set
			  update previousDgit = previousDgit+1
		try : num*10 + (previousDgit + 1) = 12*10 + (2+1) = 123
			  check if num=123 is in range of (low,high). Yes, so add to answer set.
			  update previousDgit = previousDgit+1
		try: num*10 + (previousDgit + 1) = 123*10 + (3+1) = 1234
			 check if num=1234 is in range of (low,high). No, so don't add to answer set. Notice, num>high, so break the loop.
	again, start = 2
		num = start
		previousDgit = start
		check if num=2 is in range of (low,high). No, so don't add to answer set.
		try : num*10 + (previousDgit + 1) = 2*10 + (2+1) = 23
			  check if num=23 is in range of (low,high). No, so don't add to answer set
			  update previousDgit = previousDgit+1
		try : num*10 + (previousDgit + 1) = 23*10 + (3+1) = 234
			  check if num=234 is in range of (low,high). Yes, so add to answer set.
			  update previousDgit = previousDgit+1
		try: num*10 + (previousDgit + 1) = 234*10 + (4+1) = 2345
			 check if num=2345 is in range of (low,high). No, so don't add to answer set. Notice, num>high, so break the loop.
```
similarly you can dry run other cases.
```
Note: when previous digit is 9, you can't add anymore digit to num. 
so, when previous digit is 9, break the loop.
```


Following is Java implementation
```	
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> sequentialDigits(int low, int high) {
        ArrayList<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<Integer>();
        for(int start = 1;start<=9;start++){
            int num = start, previousDigit = start;
            while(num<=high){
                if(num>=low)
                    ans.add(num);
                if(previousDigit == 9)
                    break;
                previousDigit++;
                num = num*10+previousDigit;
            }
        }
        Collections.sort(ans);
        return ans;
    }
}
```
